House Resolution 967
By: Representatives Dempsey of the 13th, Lumsden of the 12th, and Barton of the 5th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the 2025 Board of Governors Award recipient, Wanda
2 Whitten; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Wanda Whitten has been a major part of the fabric of the Rome community for
4 over 50 years; and
5 WHEREAS, during her tenure at AdventHealth Redmond, Wanda was the hospital's first
6 Director of Nutritional Services, after which she moved into the Marketing and Community
7 Relations Department serving as Director of the hospital's former H2U Senior Adult
8 Program; and
9 WHEREAS, Wanda is the former President of the Georgia Dietetic Association and former
10 President of the Southeastern Conference for Dieticians; and
11 WHEREAS, Wanda is a 22 year member of the Exchange Club of Rome, former Board
12 member and former Chair of Youth Awards, and former Chair of Santa for Seniors; and
13 WHEREAS, she has been awarded Volunteer of the Year by the Rome Club as well as
14 Georgia District Volunteer of the Year; and
