15 WHEREAS, the Exchange Club Georgia District's annual Volunteer Award is named in her
16 honor; and
17 WHEREAS, Wanda is a former Board member of Coosa Valley Fair Association, where she
18 started the Senior Ms. CVF pageant and continues to volunteer at the fair every year; and
19 WHEREAS, Wanda is a Senior Promotions Council member, former Chair of the Council,
20 and served 13 plus years as the Chair of the annual Senior Inforum; and
21 WHEREAS, Wanda is a former member of the Pilot Club of Rome, past president and
22 former Lieutenant of the Georgia District, and a former member of Rome Festivals Council;
23 and
24 WHEREAS, Wanda is a volunteer with initial years of the Rome Celebrity Dance Challenge,
25 former Executive Director of Mis Rome Competition, Miss Georgia Competition, current
26 Miss Georgia Field Director and VP of the Miss Georgia Four Points Scholarship Fund; and
27
28 WHEREAS, she is the former Event Coordinator for the Heart of the Community overseeing
29 numerous award galas and service projects including the Heart House; and
30 WHEREAS, she received the Dr. Thomas F. Frist Humanitarian Award for outstanding
31 service.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
33 the members of this body recognize Wanda Whitten for her outstanding dedication to the
34 community, commend her as a recipient of the 2025 Board of Governors Award, and extend
35 the most sincere best wishes for continued success.
